summary: The submission is for commercial property coverage on the Sunflower Hotel Group LLC (dba Cruise Resort), an eight-story, full-service resort located in Daytona Beach, Florida, with a total insured value of $100,000,000 and a requested primary limit of $6,750,000 on a replacement cost basis. The property, built in 2008 and partially renovated in 2019, comprises 240 guest rooms, multiple restaurants, bars, banquet facilities, spa, fitness center, retail, and a private marina with eight guest berths, spanning a 4.2-acre site and 198,240 square feet of building area. Construction is reinforced concrete and structural steel with a masonry exterior, concrete slab-on-grade, and a built-up membrane roof with a partial overlay completed in 2019. Major building systems include a central chilled water HVAC plant (with 2019 upgrades), a 2,500 kVA electrical service, emergency diesel generator, and full wet-pipe sprinkler fire protection. Average annual occupancy is 68%, with higher rates during the November–April high season. Insured values are allocated across buildings, contents, FF&E, public areas, mechanical systems, pools, landscaping, and marina structures.

